> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Public </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Security </ORGANIZATION> said they were `` not clear'' about the arrests. On Monday, at least 50 students from <LOCATION> Hehai </LOCATION> remained at the guest house, apparently because they still wanted to go to <LOCATION> Beijing </LOCATION>. Those who had n't been returned to their schools apparently had been moved to another hotel. Meanwhile in <LOCATION> Hangzhou </LOCATION>, capital of <LOCATION> Zhejiang </LOCATION> province, a standoff continued between 56 black Africans and Chinese at the <ORGANIZATION> Zhejiang </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agricultural </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> College </ORGANIZATION>. The students have locked themselves in their dormitory since last week because they allege <LOCATION> Chinese </LOCATION> officials say they all have AIDS. College officials have denied the claim.
